China State Grid's February Wind Turbine Accident Cuts Link to Power Grid

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-06T05:00:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/china-state-grid-s-february-wind-turbine-accident-cuts-link-to-power-grid.html
An accident caused by short circuit
at  China  State Grid Corp.’s unit in the nation’s northwest cut
links between 598 wind power turbines and the  power grid , the
State Electricity Regulatory Commission said in a statement on
its website today.  The accident, which occurred Feb. 24, had the biggest
impact on the power grid of any wind power accidents in China,
the statement said. The regulator also pointed out a number of
safety issues related to wind power generation, including
manufacturing and management of wind plants.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  